    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Works executed in the medium of wax (usually bees wax), particularly those representing objects or figures, including life-size effigies of persons, with head, hands, and bust of wax, colored and clothed to look life-like.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以蠟（通常為蜂蠟）為媒材製作的作品，更可專指呈現物體或人物的作品，包括與實體一樣大小的人物肖像，以蠟製作頭、手，與胸部，上色並為其穿著服飾，使其栩栩如生。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beelden van was (gewoonlijke bijenwas), met name beelden die objecten of personen voorstellen, vaak levensgrote beelden van personen, met hoofd, handen en buste van was, zodanig gekleurd en aangekleed dat ze levensecht zijn. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arbeit, die mit Wachs (in der Regel Bienenwachs) ausgeführt ist, besonders jene, die Objekte oder Figuren darstellen, darunter lebensgroße Bildnisse von Personen, mit Kopf, Händen und Brust aus Wachs, gefärbt und bekleidet, um lebendig auszusehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trabalhos executados com cera (geralmente cera de abelha), particularmente aqueles que representam objetos ou figuras, incluindo efígies de pessoas em tamanho natural com cabeça, mãos e busto de cera, coloridas e vestidas como se fossem reais. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
